==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torsion meter
<hw>Torsion meter</hw>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>An instrument for
determining the torque on a shaft, and hence the horse power of an
engine, esp. of a marine engine of high power, by measuring the amount
of twist of a given length of the shaft. Called also
<altname>torsimeter</altname>, <altname>torsiometer</altname>,
<altname>torsometer</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torsk</ent>⟦br⟧
